WHO   — The Greensong — the living song of the wild land that the Reds hear and run within — a green, breathing music that lets them move and hunt as part of the world rather than against it
WHAT  — the living song of the wild land that the Reds hear and run within — a green, breathing music that lets them move and hunt as part of the world rather than against it
WHERE — ALV · The Tales of Alvin Maker — Orson Scott Card (1987–2003; finale 2026)  Framework inputs: Alvin Maker; the Unmaker; the knacks; the Crystal City; the greensong  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — It is the land with a soul: the music white settlement deafens itself to, and that Ta-Kumsaw lets Alvin hear once, so he knows what is being lost.
HOW   — Crystallized from Orson Scott Card's The Tales of Alvin Maker.

